{"id":343,"date":"2026-03-07","title":"Qodo R3 — fnm ripple effects, gitleaks hardening, cross-platform globs","source":"qodo","pr":421,"patterns":["root-cause","prevention"],"fixed":10,"deferred":0,"rejected":4,"critical":2,"major":3,"minor":8,"trivial":1,"total":14,"learnings":["Root cause: fnm migration (PR #421) focused on ensure-fnm.sh wrapper but missed standalone scripts.","Prevention: Grep for `fnm env` after any fnm-related change; always pair with `fnm use`.","Root cause: Package.json test scripts written with Unix-first assumptions.","Prevention: Always use escaped double quotes (`\\\"..\\\"`) in package.json scripts for cross-platform compat.","Root cause: Defensive \"don't break the developer\" approach didn't account for security gate semantics.","Prevention: Security scanners should fail-closed; non-security tools can fail-open."]}
